Manual Process Overview – Belgium Market Document Handling
Step 1: Document Receipt & Safekeeping
The account managers or clients send physical documents via DHL. We receive an email in advance informing us that the documents are on the way. Once received, we acknowledge the DHL delivery and physically store the documents in a cupboard. We then manually update the status in the STAR system — either changing the existing status to “Received” or manually creating a new line in STAR based on the custody type.
Step 2: Document Review & Data Entry
We physically retrieve each document from the cupboard, manually scan every single page, and then review each document individually — checking every detail by hand. Based on that review, we manually upload the information into STAR and link the relevant lines in the system. If everything is in order, we proceed to the next step. If any documents are missing, we move the line to “Pending” status.
Step 3: Chasing Missing Documents
When documents are missing, we wait for the client to send them — either physically or by email. Once received, we take a physical copy and manually attach it to each and every reclaim that was missing documentation, one by one.
Step 4: Credit Advice Generation
Once all documents are complete and verified, we manually go into STAR for each individual line and generate the Credit Advice. This is done one line at a time — there is no bulk generation. Each Credit Advice is then manually downloaded, one by one.
Step 5: Physical Preparation & Dispatch
We print every Credit Advice as a physical copy. We then manually collate and attach the Credit Advice to its corresponding reclaim, along with any additional supporting documents. For AVD reclaims, we also prepare and attach individual cover letters. All the assembled documents are physically packed into a box and sent to BDA.
